An Ethiopian national was shot dead while sitting outside his shop in Bethelsdorp yesterday. Police spokeswoman Colonel Priscilla Naidu said Zellalem Sime Belauhw, 45, was sitting outside the Mama Mia Supermarket in Sanctor at about 1pm, making jokes with an unknown person. The suspect got up and started shooting at the owner. He [the suspect] then ran away, she said. Three shots were fired. Belauhw collapsed and died. Nothing was taken from the shop and the motive for the shooting is still unknown. A case of murder has been opened. Related Share on Facebook Share Share on Twitter Tweet Share on Google Plus Share